The paper discusses a deep reinforcement learning method that combines the stability of policy gradients with the efficiency of off-policy RL. This work is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), control systems (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV). However, given the focus on deep RL and policy gradients, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.RO and cs.SY for the robotics and control aspects, and cs.CV for any potential visual input.
